WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.510 --> 00:00:07.480
<i>Previously on Wild Cards...</i>

2
00:00:08.610 --> 00:00:09.180
I started volunteering
at Hemsworth Prison.

3
00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:11.080
We are gonna write.

4
00:00:11.180 --> 00:00:13.080
Thank you for making this easy.

5
00:00:13.710 --> 00:00:14.380
Me and Jessica.

6
00:00:14.480 --> 00:00:16.720
Is that what we are? A family?

7
00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:18.660
Look. Viv. I’m still
trying to process.

8
00:00:18.750 --> 00:00:21.050
You are going
to steal us a diamond.

9
00:00:22.190 --> 00:00:23.090
I know how we’re gonna
get the diamond out.

10
00:00:23.190 --> 00:00:24.690
- How?
- With magic.

11
00:00:26.830 --> 00:00:28.070
Classic.

12
00:00:29.230 --> 00:00:30.500
What’s so funny?

13
00:00:33.170 --> 00:00:35.710
Yeah. that one’s great.

14
00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:37.000
What’s got
you guys giggling?

15
00:00:40.140 --> 00:00:41.580
Oh!

16
00:00:42.310 --> 00:00:43.710
Yeah. I’ve seen this.

17
00:00:43.810 --> 00:00:44.880
Ellis. you gotta check this out.

18
00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:47.080
Hmm?

19
00:00:47.180 --> 00:00:49.120
- What am I looking at here?
- - Seriously?

20
00:00:49.220 --> 00:00:51.020
You’ve never seen the video
of Walter the Capybara

21
00:00:51.120 --> 00:00:52.620
eating an entire watermelon?

22
00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:54.090
No. I must have
missed out on this

23
00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:55.660
significant cultural moment.

24
00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:57.000
Is it fun
living under a rock?

25
00:00:57.090 --> 00:00:58.690
Yeah. you know what?
It is. actually.

26
00:00:58.790 --> 00:01:00.060
It’s nice and shady.

27
00:01:01.360 --> 00:01:04.230
What? The melons so big.
but he’s just this little guy.

28
00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:05.930
Hey. everyone.

29
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:07.130
I’m collecting money for
the children’s hospital.

30
00:01:07.230 --> 00:01:08.200
Anyone have some bucks
to throw in?

31
00:01:09.270 --> 00:01:10.170
For the kids?

32
00:01:11.600 --> 00:01:12.500
Hello?

33
00:01:13.910 --> 00:01:14.840
What the hell’s going on?

34
00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:16.740
Well. Walter is
a charming capybara.

35
00:01:16.840 --> 00:01:17.840
lives in South America.

36
00:01:17.940 --> 00:01:21.040
has a robust internet following.
and loves melons.

37
00:01:21.150 --> 00:01:22.050
I’m talking about
all of you

38
00:01:22.150 --> 00:01:24.220
buried in your cell phones
like zombies?

39
00:01:25.490 --> 00:01:26.660
You didn’t even acknowledge
Officer Toni just now.

40
00:01:26.750 --> 00:01:27.420
Hey. Toni.

41
00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:28.920
- Hi. Toni.
- Sorry. Toni.

42
00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:30.090
I’m just gonna leave this here.

43
00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:32.160
Thank you. Toni.
Donation jar.

44
00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:34.490
Look. Chief.
we got a little downtime.

45
00:01:34.590 --> 00:01:36.060
Yates and I are still waiting
on ballistics to get back

46
00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:37.190
on one of our cases.

47
00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:38.900
Simmons. it’s about what
you do with your downtime.

48
00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:40.900
Whatever happened
to connecting? Talking?

49
00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:42.740
Making eye contact
with each other?

50
00:01:42.840 --> 00:01:44.810
No offense. sir.
but you sound really elderly.

51
00:01:44.900 --> 00:01:45.670
I mean. it’s bad.

52
00:01:45.770 --> 00:01:46.770
Nobody asked.
Stop talking.

53
00:01:46.870 --> 00:01:49.170
Max. Ellis. get down
to the waterfront.

54
00:01:50.240 --> 00:01:51.210
A body just got pulled
from the water.

55
00:01:51.310 --> 00:01:52.950
Yates. Simmons. find something
productive to do

56
00:01:53.050 --> 00:01:53.820
with your downtime.

57
00:01:53.910 --> 00:01:55.280
- Yep. Can do. sir.
- Copy that.

58
00:01:55.880 --> 00:01:56.910
Doing it now.

59
00:01:58.120 --> 00:02:00.220
Hey. have you seen
the Japanese weasel. Alfred?

60
00:02:01.090 --> 00:02:01.760
Oh. I love that little weasel.

61
00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:02.890
You ever seen him in a tuxedo?

62
00:02:02.990 --> 00:02:04.260
Now!

63
00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:07.060
In plastic jars.

64
00:02:07.690 --> 00:02:09.230
Silence ferments.

65
00:02:09.830 --> 00:02:11.000
Sharp rebellion.

66
00:02:11.100 --> 00:02:12.230
Masked intents.

67
00:02:12.870 --> 00:02:13.970
Sip of freedom.

68
00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:15.140
Harsh and raw.

69
00:02:15.900 --> 00:02:17.240
Taste of night.

70
00:02:17.870 --> 00:02:18.700
Beyond the law.

71
00:02:22.340 --> 00:02:24.140
Thanks for sharing that. Ralph.

72
00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:26.310
Who knew prison hooch
could be so poetic.

73
00:02:28.750 --> 00:02:30.220
So anyone else want
to share anything?

74
00:02:31.050 --> 00:02:31.920
Tell us what you wrote about

75
00:02:32.020 --> 00:02:32.890
or even get something
off your chest?

76
00:02:34.290 --> 00:02:35.630
Paul’s got something to say.

77
00:02:36.390 --> 00:02:37.730
Come on. man.

78
00:02:38.890 --> 00:02:40.590
He’s getting released
and he’s freaking out.

79
00:02:41.460 --> 00:02:42.800
You want to talk about it. Paul?

80
00:02:42.900 --> 00:02:45.270
They told me yesterday
I’m getting out next week.

81
00:02:46.470 --> 00:02:48.210
It’s not supposed to be
another few years. even.

82
00:02:48.300 --> 00:02:49.800
Now. don’t think
I’m not grateful. guys.

83
00:02:49.900 --> 00:02:50.930
I know I’m lucky.

84
00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:53.340
I just thought I’d have
more time to. you know.

85
00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:54.910
get ready to go face things.

86
00:02:55.010 --> 00:02:56.080
But now I gotta leave.

87
00:02:56.180 --> 00:02:58.120
get a place. get a job.

88
00:02:58.210 --> 00:03:00.250
Avoid all the bad things
from my past life.

89
00:03:00.350 --> 00:03:01.750
Reconnect with the good.

90
00:03:01.850 --> 00:03:03.750
How does anybody do that?

91
00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:04.920
You’ve done it. George.

92
00:03:05.020 --> 00:03:06.090
You’re out.
How you doing?

93
00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:07.730
Me? Well...

94
00:03:08.860 --> 00:03:10.360
the first time you wake up
and you realize

95
00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:13.260
the day is yours feels like
winning the lottery.

96
00:03:13.990 --> 00:03:14.960
I mean. sure. it’s work.

97
00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:16.330
Finding a place. finding a job.

98
00:03:16.430 --> 00:03:18.300
But it’s also freedom.

99
00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:19.800
Real freedom.

100
00:03:19.900 --> 00:03:21.370
And what could
be better than that?

101
00:03:22.040 --> 00:03:22.810
So how am I doing?

102
00:03:23.400 --> 00:03:24.370
I’m doing great.

103
00:03:25.340 --> 00:03:26.780
And you will too.

104
00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:34.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

105
00:03:38.050 --> 00:03:39.320
He was pulled from
the water early this morning.

106
00:03:39.420 --> 00:03:40.420
A male in his 30’s.

107
00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:41.820
How long
has he been dead for?

108
00:03:41.920 --> 00:03:45.090
Hard to say. given he’s been
in the water for a while.

109
00:03:45.190 --> 00:03:46.160
A week. maybe?

110
00:03:46.760 --> 00:03:47.290
Did he drown?

111
00:03:47.960 --> 00:03:49.160
Nope. He was shot.

112
00:03:49.260 --> 00:03:51.900
One bullet went right through.
the other still in his body.

113
00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:54.400
The bruising indicates the
body was dumped in the water.

114
00:03:55.100 --> 00:03:56.170
but the weird part?

115
00:03:56.270 --> 00:03:58.340
He’s short an index finger.

116
00:03:59.410 --> 00:04:01.110
- It’s a recent cut.
- Is there any way

117
00:04:01.210 --> 00:04:03.010
the finger could have been
cut off in the past week?

118
00:04:03.110 --> 00:04:04.410
Maybe by the current
or something in the water?

119
00:04:05.040 --> 00:04:05.970
It’s a clean cut.

120
00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:07.550
Likely done with shears.
maybe bolt cutters.

121
00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:09.750
So you’re saying the finger
was cut off intentionally?

122
00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:11.080
That’s exactly what I’m saying.

123
00:04:12.220 --> 00:04:13.690
Is it too soon
for a "pull my finger" joke?

124
00:04:21.890 --> 00:04:24.230
{\an8}Our victim. Cornelius Cooper.

125
00:04:24.330 --> 00:04:26.300
{\an8} We matched the body
to a missing persons report

126
00:04:27.370 --> 00:04:28.070
{\an8}filed by his sister
about a month ago.

127
00:04:28.170 --> 00:04:29.170
{\an8}Does the sister have any leads?

128
00:04:29.270 --> 00:04:30.340
{\an8}No. She lives out of town.

129
00:04:30.440 --> 00:04:32.340
{\an8} When she found out
his cell phone was deactivated.

130
00:04:32.440 --> 00:04:34.340
{\an8} she called his work.
Turns out he quit weeks ago.

131
00:04:34.440 --> 00:04:36.980
{\an8} Yeah. the guy’s got
no partner and zero friends.

132
00:04:37.080 --> 00:04:39.280
{\an8}He worked at a tech startup
called SociaScope.

133
00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:41.180
{\an8}Okay. you and Ellis
bring the boss in.

134
00:04:41.280 --> 00:04:42.880
{\an8}- See what you can find out.
- Got it.

135
00:04:42.980 --> 00:04:44.320
{\an8} Simmons. Yates.
dig into Cornelius’s past.

136
00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:46.150
{\an8}Check in with organized crime.

137
00:04:46.250 --> 00:04:48.090
{\an8}See if the missing finger
fits any mob M.O.’s

138
00:04:48.190 --> 00:04:49.160
{\an8}All right. you got it.

139
00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:55.130
{\an8} Hey. Ronan.
Thanks for coming in.

140
00:04:55.230 --> 00:04:56.470
{\an8}Hey. My pleasure.

141
00:04:56.560 --> 00:04:59.360
{\an8}Now. you were Cornelius’s boss
at SociaScope. is that right?

142
00:04:59.470 --> 00:05:02.040
{\an8}Yeah. Man. I can’t believe
Cornelius was murdered.

143
00:05:02.140 --> 00:05:04.010
{\an8}How long have you been
CEO at SociaScope?

144
00:05:04.100 --> 00:05:06.970
{\an8} Oh. I got the idea in my
sophomore year of college.

145
00:05:07.070 --> 00:05:09.910
{\an8} A year and 100 million
in venture capital later. and...

146
00:05:10.010 --> 00:05:11.010
{\an8}SociaScope was born.

147
00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:12.480
{\an8}So what is SociaScope?

148
00:05:12.580 --> 00:05:14.350
{\an8}SociaScope aggregates
your social media

149
00:05:15.620 --> 00:05:17.490
{\an8} to automate messages
to your friends in your voice.

150
00:05:17.580 --> 00:05:19.350
{\an8}so you don’t have to keep up
with conversations

151
00:05:19.450 --> 00:05:21.350
{\an8}or birthday greetings
ever again.

152
00:05:21.450 --> 00:05:23.490
{\an8}It maintains your relationships
at the touch of a button.

153
00:05:24.460 --> 00:05:25.490
{\an8}Well. it’s not you.
It’s an app.

154
00:05:26.230 --> 00:05:28.030
{\an8}Well. the app is you.

155
00:05:28.130 --> 00:05:29.500
{\an8}Can you tell us more
about Cornelius?

156
00:05:29.600 --> 00:05:31.370
{\an8}- What was he like?
- Real tech savant.

157
00:05:31.460 --> 00:05:33.130
{\an8}He perfected an algorithm
to keep people

158
00:05:33.230 --> 00:05:35.030
{\an8}on the app 33 percent longer.

159
00:05:35.740 --> 00:05:36.980
{\an8}Total game changer.

160
00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:38.770
{\an8}Cornelius would have been set
for life here if he hadn’t...

161
00:05:39.640 --> 00:05:41.510
{\an8}you know. gone off the deep end.

162
00:05:41.610 --> 00:05:42.740
{\an8}What do you mean.
"the deep end"?

163
00:05:42.840 --> 00:05:44.440
{\an8} Well. first he stopped
coming in to the office.

164
00:05:45.210 --> 00:05:46.240
{\an8}working more from home.

165
00:05:46.350 --> 00:05:47.990
{\an8} and dropped the ball
on some major presentations.

166
00:05:48.080 --> 00:05:50.420
{\an8} And one day he sends an
email to the whole company.

167
00:05:51.250 --> 00:05:52.350
{\an8}A 50-page mission statement.

168
00:05:52.450 --> 00:05:54.120
{\an8} - What was in it?
- Basically. it was like

169
00:05:54.220 --> 00:05:56.520
"SociaScope is evil".
blah blah blah.

170
00:05:56.620 --> 00:05:58.460
"It’s driving people apart".
blah blah blah.

171
00:05:59.230 --> 00:06:00.260
He sent this to everyone.

172
00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:01.960
Well. sounds like he went
full-blown Jerry Maguire.

173
00:06:03.060 --> 00:06:03.990
- Who’s that?
- Are you serious?

174
00:06:04.100 --> 00:06:06.170
"Who’s coming with me?"
"You complete me."

175
00:06:06.270 --> 00:06:07.270
"You had me at hello."

176
00:06:08.230 --> 00:06:09.470
Forget it.
Can you think of anybody

177
00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:11.300
who might have wanted
to kill Cornelius?

178
00:06:11.400 --> 00:06:12.370
No clue.

179
00:06:12.470 --> 00:06:13.300
He was a pretty chill dude.

180
00:06:13.410 --> 00:06:14.750
other than his big.
weird document.

181
00:06:14.840 --> 00:06:16.910
Speaking of which. we’re
gonna need a copy of that.

182
00:06:18.950 --> 00:06:19.980
"The digital world

183
00:06:20.080 --> 00:06:23.080
"has disconnected us under
the guise of connection.

184
00:06:23.180 --> 00:06:26.520
"Big tech has made us more
isolated and alone than ever."

185
00:06:27.150 --> 00:06:27.980
I don’t disagree.

186
00:06:28.090 --> 00:06:29.220
We’re all way
too glued to our phones.

187
00:06:29.320 --> 00:06:30.290
Oh. Here’s something.

188
00:06:30.390 --> 00:06:33.260
He also mentions a woman
named Celeste Rainier.

189
00:06:33.360 --> 00:06:36.260
Looks like she started
a group called The Apiary.

190
00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:38.500
<i> An apiary is
a collection of beehives</i>

191
00:06:39.800 --> 00:06:41.500
<i> sharing resources
and cooperating with each other.</i>

192
00:06:42.600 --> 00:06:44.400
<i>And the great queen bee
rules them all.</i>

193
00:06:44.500 --> 00:06:47.440
<i>For bees. connection is key.
but as humans.</i>

194
00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:49.280
<i>we’ve become disconnected.</i>

195
00:06:49.380 --> 00:06:51.550
<i>isolated because of technology.</i>

196
00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:55.240
<i> I’m Celeste Rainier.
and I used to be just like you.</i>

197
00:06:55.350 --> 00:06:57.390
<i>Lonely. Depressed. Unsure.</i>

198
00:06:57.480 --> 00:06:58.480
<i>I worked in tech.</i>

199
00:06:58.580 --> 00:07:00.580
<i>contributing to the devolution
of society.</i>

200
00:07:01.450 --> 00:07:02.420
<i>but longing for connection.</i>

201
00:07:03.520 --> 00:07:06.120
<i> And that’s why
I started The Apiary.</i>

202
00:07:06.230 --> 00:07:07.500
Yeah. I’d swipe right on her.

203
00:07:07.590 --> 00:07:08.990
- Yates.
- What?

204
00:07:09.100 --> 00:07:10.540
She’s foxy. sir.
and I have eyes.

205
00:07:11.530 --> 00:07:13.570
Okay. What exactly is
The Apiary?

206
00:07:14.730 --> 00:07:16.500
Uh. they call themselves
a digital detox retreat.

207
00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:19.600
They claim to help people
reconnect away from technology.

208
00:07:19.710 --> 00:07:21.510
According to Cornelius’s
financial records.

209
00:07:22.240 --> 00:07:23.210
he joined six months ago

210
00:07:23.310 --> 00:07:24.480
and transferred
his savings to them.

211
00:07:24.580 --> 00:07:27.050
Yeah. Last month. he moved
into their compound full time.

212
00:07:27.150 --> 00:07:27.920
That sounds fishy.

213
00:07:28.010 --> 00:07:29.180
Yeah. that’s what
we thought too.

214
00:07:29.280 --> 00:07:30.310
So we did a little digging.

215
00:07:30.420 --> 00:07:32.160
Tess Harwell. a former member.

216
00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:33.620
she’s trying to sue Celeste
and The Apiary.

217
00:07:34.090 --> 00:07:34.920
Why?

218
00:07:35.020 --> 00:07:37.320
Tess thinks The Apiary is...
a cult.

219
00:07:37.420 --> 00:07:38.620
If it is. in fact. a cult.

220
00:07:39.690 --> 00:07:40.930
there’s guaranteed
sex stuff going on.

221
00:07:42.030 --> 00:07:43.130
Okay. we’ll take this one
off your hands.

222
00:07:43.230 --> 00:07:44.360
Sit down.

223
00:07:44.460 --> 00:07:46.230
Ellis. Max. bring in Tess.

224
00:07:46.330 --> 00:07:47.460
Get the full story.

225
00:07:47.570 --> 00:07:50.040
Hey. if you all need backup.
you know where to find me.

226
00:07:50.140 --> 00:07:51.480
- Yeah.
- Sorry. Yeah.

227
00:07:51.570 --> 00:07:53.510
How did you become
a member of The Apiary?

228
00:07:53.610 --> 00:07:55.050
I used to work in tech.

229
00:07:55.140 --> 00:07:56.610
I’d code for 16 hours a day.

230
00:07:57.610 --> 00:07:59.210
then go home
and scroll all night.

231
00:07:59.310 --> 00:08:01.150
I mean. I had thousands
of digital connections.

232
00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:02.180
but no real friends.

233
00:08:02.280 --> 00:08:03.450
When I joined The Apiary.

234
00:08:03.550 --> 00:08:05.090
I thought
I’d get back to nature.

235
00:08:05.180 --> 00:08:06.550
Forge real human connections.

236
00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:08.590
And at first I did.

237
00:08:08.690 --> 00:08:11.390
How does The Apiary work.
exactly?

238
00:08:11.490 --> 00:08:12.520
Well. there
are different levels.

239
00:08:12.630 --> 00:08:13.660
You start off as a drone.

240
00:08:13.760 --> 00:08:16.560
The hope is that you will
ascend to worker level.

241
00:08:16.660 --> 00:08:18.530
Those are the members of
Celeste’s inner circle.

242
00:08:18.630 --> 00:08:20.530
Let me guess.
Celeste is the queen bee?

243
00:08:20.630 --> 00:08:21.460
Is she ever.

244
00:08:21.570 --> 00:08:24.210
Everyone treats her
like she’s a god.

245
00:08:24.300 --> 00:08:26.340
They’re desperate to ascend
to worker level.

246
00:08:26.440 --> 00:08:27.570
And how does that
exactly happen?

247
00:08:28.340 --> 00:08:29.270
Well. it’s almost random.

248
00:08:29.380 --> 00:08:31.350
Maybe they prove
their loyalty to Celeste.

249
00:08:31.440 --> 00:08:32.680
or maybe they donate
to The Apiary.

250
00:08:33.710 --> 00:08:34.540
Or maybe they excel
in the workshops.

251
00:08:35.880 --> 00:08:37.680
What kind of workshops?
Like watercolour class or...?

252
00:08:38.220 --> 00:08:39.290
It varies.

253
00:08:39.390 --> 00:08:41.390
Some workshops are innocuous
team-building exercises.

254
00:08:42.390 --> 00:08:44.560
Some workshops are more intense.

255
00:08:45.060 --> 00:08:45.660
How so?

256
00:08:45.760 --> 00:08:47.630
Some of them involve pain.

257
00:08:48.930 --> 00:08:50.570
There’s one with hot coals.
another with ice water.

258
00:08:50.660 --> 00:08:52.400
They say these weed out
the non devout.

259
00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:55.100
but really it’s just a way
of controlling people.

260
00:08:55.200 --> 00:08:57.370
Because trust me.
In there. you...

261
00:08:57.470 --> 00:08:58.710
you want Celeste’s approval.

262
00:08:59.940 --> 00:09:02.180
I ended up forking over
all of my life savings.

263
00:09:02.280 --> 00:09:04.680
hoping that she would
look at me favorably.

264
00:09:05.410 --> 00:09:06.510
You were brainwashed.

265
00:09:07.580 --> 00:09:09.450
You mentioned things happening
at night.

266
00:09:09.550 --> 00:09:10.680
What do you mean?

267
00:09:10.780 --> 00:09:12.720
You aren’t allowed to leave
your lodging after curfew.

268
00:09:12.820 --> 00:09:15.260
They say it’s to get a good
sleep. but really.

269
00:09:15.350 --> 00:09:16.720
it’s so Celeste
and the worker bees

270
00:09:17.420 --> 00:09:18.320
can meet in secret.

271
00:09:18.420 --> 00:09:19.690
- How did you know that?
- Because

272
00:09:19.790 --> 00:09:21.260
one night I snuck out
and I followed them

273
00:09:21.360 --> 00:09:22.390
to the meeting house.

274
00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:24.140
I heard them talking about
some sort of mission.

275
00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:25.260
They called it a harvest.

276
00:09:25.360 --> 00:09:27.660
but Kurt caught me
before I could find out more.

277
00:09:27.770 --> 00:09:29.610
- Who’s Kurt?
- Celeste’s right-hand man.

278
00:09:29.700 --> 00:09:30.500
He’s technically a worker bee.

279
00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:32.200
but she trusts him
more than anyone.

280
00:09:32.310 --> 00:09:33.480
He’s been with her
from the start.

281
00:09:33.570 --> 00:09:35.240
And what happened
when he found you?

282
00:09:35.340 --> 00:09:36.270
I snapped.

283
00:09:36.380 --> 00:09:38.650
I told him there
are sketchy things going on.

284
00:09:38.740 --> 00:09:40.740
and someone ought to find out
what they’re doing in there.

285
00:09:41.610 --> 00:09:42.340
He kicked me out on the spot.

286
00:09:42.450 --> 00:09:43.580
Now. in your time there.

287
00:09:43.680 --> 00:09:45.680
did you ever run into someone
named Cornelius Cooper?

288
00:09:45.790 --> 00:09:47.260
I didn’t.
Is he a member?

289
00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:48.550
Not anymore.
He was found dead.

290
00:09:48.650 --> 00:09:50.390
Oh my God.
Wait. you think...

291
00:09:50.490 --> 00:09:51.490
they killed him?

292
00:09:51.590 --> 00:09:53.630
Well. we’re still early
in our investigation.

293
00:09:53.730 --> 00:09:55.470
but hopefully
the information you just shared

294
00:09:55.560 --> 00:09:56.900
will help us figure that out.

295
00:09:58.060 --> 00:09:59.090
Well. if you want
to question them. forget it.

296
00:10:00.570 --> 00:10:02.370
Celeste has a hold on everyone.
even the people who have left.

297
00:10:02.470 --> 00:10:04.240
I’ve been building
a civil suit for months.

298
00:10:04.340 --> 00:10:06.310
and no one is willing to talk.

299
00:10:06.410 --> 00:10:07.780
Or they’re too afraid.

300
00:10:09.210 --> 00:10:10.310
The only way to find out what’s
going on is from the inside.

301
00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:15.280
Yeah. Everything’s
trucking along.

302
00:10:15.380 --> 00:10:17.080
Prison support
group is going well.

303
00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:20.190
Life is. you know. life-ing.

304
00:10:20.290 --> 00:10:20.790
Okay.

305
00:10:21.550 --> 00:10:23.150
But tell me. George.

306
00:10:24.120 --> 00:10:24.690
How are you?

307
00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:26.160
Me?

308
00:10:26.260 --> 00:10:28.230
Well. I got no complaints.
Everything’s great.

309
00:10:28.330 --> 00:10:29.330
Really?

310
00:10:29.430 --> 00:10:31.270
Of course.

311
00:10:31.360 --> 00:10:33.430
It’s just that
I’ve noticed that

312
00:10:33.530 --> 00:10:34.400
whenever we talk.

313
00:10:34.500 --> 00:10:36.700
you reassure me
how great everything is.

314
00:10:36.800 --> 00:10:39.670
But you’re still adjusting
to life on the outside.

315
00:10:39.770 --> 00:10:40.700
People often feel

316
00:10:40.810 --> 00:10:43.780
profound disconnection
while they readjust.

317
00:10:43.880 --> 00:10:46.280
I just want you to know that
as your parole officer.

318
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:48.480
I’m not just here to keep you
on the straight and narrow.

319
00:10:49.350 --> 00:10:50.480
I’m also an ear.

320
00:10:50.580 --> 00:10:52.220
Well. thanks. But--

321
00:10:52.320 --> 00:10:54.460
You might feel
you need to be great.

322
00:10:54.550 --> 00:10:55.680
you know. for all the people
in your life.

323
00:10:56.490 --> 00:10:57.620
But me? I don’t need that.

324
00:10:58.490 --> 00:10:59.490
I just need you to be George.

325
00:11:01.830 --> 00:11:03.700
All right. Tess was right.

326
00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:04.830
Yates and I went out

327
00:11:04.930 --> 00:11:06.770
to The Apiary’s property.
and we got stonewalled.

328
00:11:06.870 --> 00:11:08.570
Even former members
we tracked down.

329
00:11:08.670 --> 00:11:09.670
They won’t talk to us.

330
00:11:09.770 --> 00:11:11.840
But they all collectively
seemed very freaked out.

331
00:11:11.940 --> 00:11:13.810
Don’t they have to talk to us?
We’re the police?

332
00:11:15.040 --> 00:11:16.380
The Apiary’s essentially
made itself into a church.

333
00:11:16.480 --> 00:11:18.850
They can claim religious
freedoms to protect themselves.

334
00:11:18.940 --> 00:11:20.810
Yeah. but that
only goes so far. legally.

335
00:11:20.910 --> 00:11:21.980
I mean. even at entry level.

336
00:11:22.080 --> 00:11:23.550
we know they’re doing
nefarious things.

337
00:11:23.650 --> 00:11:25.320
Imagine what’s happening
behind closed doors.

338
00:11:25.420 --> 00:11:27.460
You’re right. Skin branding.
Kool-Aid drinking.

339
00:11:27.550 --> 00:11:28.450
cannibalism.

340
00:11:28.550 --> 00:11:30.790
Celeste might have eaten
Cornelius’s finger

341
00:11:30.890 --> 00:11:32.560
with fava beans
and a nice Chianti.

342
00:11:32.660 --> 00:11:33.630
Look. it’s like Tess said.

343
00:11:33.730 --> 00:11:35.570
The only shot of getting
evidence against them

344
00:11:35.660 --> 00:11:37.830
is to go in. become people
that Celeste can trust.

345
00:11:38.960 --> 00:11:39.590
Are you saying what
I think you’re saying?

346
00:11:39.700 --> 00:11:40.470
That’s right.

347
00:11:40.570 --> 00:11:42.140
I think it’s time
we join a cult.

348
00:11:42.940 --> 00:11:43.870
- Let’s go!
- Not you.

349
00:11:44.340 --> 00:11:45.140
Fine.

350
00:11:50.810 --> 00:11:53.480
♪<i> Here’s to the one
who came out for love</i> ♪

351
00:11:53.580 --> 00:11:55.620
♪<i> Love me</i> ♪

352
00:11:55.720 --> 00:11:57.490
♪<i> Isn’t it the one?</i> ♪

353
00:11:57.580 --> 00:12:01.850
♪<i> All little things
come back now to haunt me</i> ♪

354
00:12:02.960 --> 00:12:04.600
♪<i> Isn’t it the one?</i> ♪

355
00:12:09.260 --> 00:12:11.460
Ah. It’s like
the first day of school.

356
00:12:11.560 --> 00:12:14.230
Except instead of school
it’s a maybe murderous cult.

357
00:12:14.830 --> 00:12:16.330
So game plan?

358
00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:17.810
Right. Game plan.

359
00:12:19.210 --> 00:12:21.610
Connect with Apiary members.
find anyone who knew Cornelius

360
00:12:21.710 --> 00:12:23.480
and see what information
we can get from them.

361
00:12:23.580 --> 00:12:25.550
See if anyone’s missing
any critical digits?

362
00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:26.610
Right. but we gotta
be careful. okay?

363
00:12:26.710 --> 00:12:28.610
We don’t know what these
people are capable of.

364
00:12:28.710 --> 00:12:30.480
But more importantly.
let’s discuss our characters.

365
00:12:30.580 --> 00:12:31.380
Because I made a change to mine.

366
00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:34.350
I’m Beth. a nervous.
introverted geek

367
00:12:34.450 --> 00:12:35.690
who’s desperate for community.

368
00:12:35.790 --> 00:12:36.820
That’s what you said you were
going as.

369
00:12:37.520 --> 00:12:37.790
What did you change?

370
00:12:38.520 --> 00:12:39.420
I changed my glasses.

371
00:12:39.530 --> 00:12:40.630
These ones are much cuter.
Don’t you think?

372
00:12:40.730 --> 00:12:41.730
Oh. yeah. Huge difference.

373
00:12:41.830 --> 00:12:42.930
It’s all about the details.

374
00:12:43.030 --> 00:12:44.900
What did you say your
character name was again? Helen?

375
00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:46.130
Dylan.

376
00:12:46.230 --> 00:12:47.800
Single father.
out of sorts since my divorce.

377
00:12:47.900 --> 00:12:48.900
searching for meaning.

378
00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:50.500
Oh. Sad dad. Good call.

379
00:12:50.600 --> 00:12:52.340
Okay. break.

380
00:12:52.440 --> 00:12:54.940
Hello and welcome to The Apiary.

381
00:12:55.780 --> 00:12:58.420
I’m Kurt. and this is Fiona.

382
00:12:58.510 --> 00:12:59.810
On behalf of Celeste.
I’m honoured

383
00:13:00.680 --> 00:13:01.810
to welcome you to our community.

384
00:13:01.910 --> 00:13:05.180
To start. you must relinquish
your phones to Fiona.

385
00:13:06.220 --> 00:13:07.890
This is a core tenant
of The Apiary.

386
00:13:09.360 --> 00:13:10.490
Congratulations.

387
00:13:11.660 --> 00:13:13.360
You have all taken
the first step to freedom.

388
00:13:14.530 --> 00:13:16.630
Now. the men will follow me
to your lodgings.

389
00:13:16.730 --> 00:13:18.430
and the women
will go with Fiona.

390
00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:20.370
This way. ladies.

391
00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:22.800
Take it all in.

392
00:13:23.370 --> 00:13:24.370
Breathe.

393
00:13:25.370 --> 00:13:26.710
You’ve come
here seeking renewal.

394
00:13:26.810 --> 00:13:27.840
because you knew

395
00:13:28.840 --> 00:13:30.840
deep down
that a better way existed.

396
00:13:30.940 --> 00:13:33.710
And that better way
is here at The Apiary.

397
00:13:35.710 --> 00:13:37.480
Here are the men’s lodgings.

398
00:13:38.750 --> 00:13:40.850
For those of you that opted
for a private sanctuary.

399
00:13:41.720 --> 00:13:41.990
you’ll find them to the left.

400
00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:43.850
Oh! I have one of those.

401
00:13:44.620 --> 00:13:45.960
Oh. sorry.

402
00:13:46.990 --> 00:13:47.920
I’ll shut up.
I’m just really excited.

403
00:13:48.030 --> 00:13:49.100
It’s okay.

404
00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:50.940
It’s a lot of stimulation
arriving here.

405
00:13:52.300 --> 00:13:53.600
especially for people who spend
most of their time alone.

406
00:13:53.700 --> 00:13:54.870
Guilty as charged.

407
00:13:54.970 --> 00:13:57.610
The workshops introduce you
to The Apiary’s way of life.

408
00:13:57.700 --> 00:13:58.970
This is to ensure
that you experience

409
00:14:00.010 --> 00:14:00.980
the proper benefits
of sleep hygiene.

410
00:14:02.010 --> 00:14:03.250
Any questions?

411
00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:05.420
It all sounds really great.

412
00:14:05.510 --> 00:14:06.280
Good.

413
00:14:06.810 --> 00:14:07.710
Over here.

414
00:14:09.110 --> 00:14:11.610
If you’ve opted
for a private sanctuary.

415
00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:13.720
you will find those to the left.

416
00:14:14.920 --> 00:14:15.790
Yeah. That’s me.

417
00:14:15.890 --> 00:14:18.560
As per your signed
community agreement.

418
00:14:18.660 --> 00:14:20.600
it is forbidden

419
00:14:20.690 --> 00:14:22.890
for you to exit
your lodging after curfew.

420
00:14:23.660 --> 00:14:25.000
Please change immediately

421
00:14:25.100 --> 00:14:26.770
and proceed
to your welcome session.

422
00:14:35.880 --> 00:14:38.350
Ah. What do you think
the hold-up is?

423
00:14:39.040 --> 00:14:40.010
It’s taking a while.

424
00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:42.480
Are we even in the right spot?

425
00:14:42.580 --> 00:14:44.850
I don’t want them to get mad at
us for being in the wrong place.

426
00:14:44.950 --> 00:14:46.490
I wonder if there’s a spa here.

427
00:14:46.590 --> 00:14:48.330
I could sure use
a facial extraction.

428
00:14:49.150 --> 00:14:51.050
Or a massage. Or a colonic.

429
00:14:51.160 --> 00:14:52.560
Hopefully not at the same time.

430
00:14:53.730 --> 00:14:54.860
I really like these outfits.

431
00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:57.030
They’re very... yellow.

432
00:14:57.130 --> 00:14:58.030
Shh!

433
00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:14.550
Welcome everyone.

434
00:15:14.650 --> 00:15:15.580
I am Celeste.

435
00:15:15.680 --> 00:15:18.850
It is such an honour
to welcome my new brood.

436
00:15:18.950 --> 00:15:20.050
And congratulations!

437
00:15:20.150 --> 00:15:22.950
You have just completed
your first Apiary workshop.

438
00:15:24.220 --> 00:15:26.620
I know what you’re thinking.
Weren’t we just waiting?

439
00:15:26.730 --> 00:15:27.560
And you’re right.

440
00:15:28.430 --> 00:15:29.830
It wasn’t so easy. was it?

441
00:15:31.060 --> 00:15:33.060
Did some of you
experience fidgeting?

442
00:15:33.930 --> 00:15:34.960
Tapping? Mindless chattering?

443
00:15:36.540 --> 00:15:37.370
Ah.

444
00:15:38.570 --> 00:15:39.940
We have a winner. do we?

445
00:15:40.670 --> 00:15:42.110
I’m just really nervous.

446
00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:44.080
And when I get nervous.
I ramble.

447
00:15:45.240 --> 00:15:47.610
And when I start rambling.
I just can’t stop.

448
00:15:47.710 --> 00:15:48.640
Like right now?

449
00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:50.850
Yeah. exactly. Sorry.

450
00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:51.820
No need to apologize.

451
00:15:51.920 --> 00:15:53.990
These are signs
of digital withdrawal.

452
00:15:54.090 --> 00:15:55.090
Without even knowing it.

453
00:15:55.190 --> 00:15:58.130
you’re constantly seeking
another dopamine hit.

454
00:15:59.220 --> 00:16:01.560
It’s an addiction.
Like drugs or alcohol.

455
00:16:04.100 --> 00:16:05.900
Think about when you were
a young child.

456
00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:07.640
You were living in the moment.

457
00:16:07.730 --> 00:16:08.530
You weren’t thinking about

458
00:16:08.630 --> 00:16:10.600
recording it
for a social media post.

459
00:16:11.340 --> 00:16:12.780
Now ask yourself this.

460
00:16:12.870 --> 00:16:15.410
Were you happier
living in the moment?

461
00:16:17.640 --> 00:16:19.610
That’s why you came
to The Apiary.

462
00:16:19.710 --> 00:16:21.480
To find that person again.

463
00:16:22.650 --> 00:16:24.090
You will experience
some discomfort at first.

464
00:16:25.150 --> 00:16:26.690
but soon you will discover
true peace.

465
00:16:26.790 --> 00:16:29.160
And I will help you heal.
if you’ll let me.

466
00:16:30.160 --> 00:16:30.960
Now. proceed
to your next workshop.

467
00:16:31.060 --> 00:16:32.830
and welcome to The Apiary.

468
00:16:41.530 --> 00:16:43.170
Celeste sure knows how to win
over a crowd.

469
00:16:44.240 --> 00:16:46.080
That’s for sure.
I’d drink her Kool-Aid.

470
00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:48.040
All right.
I’m gonna focus on Kurt.

471
00:16:48.140 --> 00:16:50.040
Celeste’s right-hand man.
See what I can find out.

472
00:16:50.710 --> 00:16:51.540
Okay. I got Fiona.

473
00:16:51.640 --> 00:16:53.640
Let’s call it
Operation Minion Mingle.

474
00:16:54.850 --> 00:16:58.120
So what’s this workshop
supposed to help with?

475
00:16:59.390 --> 00:17:00.690
Well. because of technology.
we’ve lost the ability

476
00:17:00.790 --> 00:17:02.130
to look each other in the eye.

477
00:17:03.490 --> 00:17:06.460
This helps us get reacquainted
with each other’s essence.

478
00:17:07.490 --> 00:17:09.830
What brought you
to The Apiary. Fiona?

479
00:17:10.700 --> 00:17:12.040
I used to code for a dating app.

480
00:17:12.130 --> 00:17:16.200
We reduce humans to data points.
and it felt... awful.

481
00:17:17.200 --> 00:17:19.070
So then when I joined
The Apiary.

482
00:17:19.170 --> 00:17:22.870
it was like someone
had turned all the lights on.

483
00:17:22.980 --> 00:17:25.180
And I had no idea
how lost I was until then.

484
00:17:26.210 --> 00:17:28.150
And you like it here?
You feel safe?

485
00:17:28.680 --> 00:17:29.780
Of course.

486
00:17:29.880 --> 00:17:32.950
I experienced joy now
in a way I have never before.

487
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:34.850
You’ll feel it soon. too.

488
00:17:34.950 --> 00:17:36.190
It’s pretty cool
that so many people here

489
00:17:36.920 --> 00:17:38.050
used to work in tech.

490
00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:40.630
We’ve all seen from the
inside how tech is ruining us.

491
00:17:40.730 --> 00:17:43.630
It’s time to take
responsibility and change it.

492
00:17:43.730 --> 00:17:44.970
Makes sense.

493
00:17:45.060 --> 00:17:47.860
I mean. I heard of The Apiary
from someone who works in tech

494
00:17:47.970 --> 00:17:48.770
at a conference.

495
00:17:48.870 --> 00:17:51.640
I think his name was...
Cornelius?

496
00:17:56.710 --> 00:17:58.050
I do not know that name.

497
00:18:00.650 --> 00:18:02.190
You’ve reached five minutes.

498
00:18:03.450 --> 00:18:06.820
Five minutes of having
your hand submerged in water

499
00:18:06.920 --> 00:18:08.690
ten degrees below freezing.

500
00:18:14.090 --> 00:18:16.830
The night Celeste stepped away
from the tech world.

501
00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:19.270
she felt driven mad
by disconnection.

502
00:18:19.360 --> 00:18:23.060
Suddenly. she prepared a bowl
of water just as cold as this

503
00:18:23.170 --> 00:18:24.270
and submerged her hand.

504
00:18:24.370 --> 00:18:26.240
And in the searing pain.

505
00:18:26.340 --> 00:18:28.810
she saw the truth
of what she must do.

506
00:18:29.440 --> 00:18:30.240
Start The Apiary.

507
00:18:32.110 --> 00:18:34.780
Jeff. you have chosen
not to complete the exercise.

508
00:18:34.880 --> 00:18:36.920
I came here to stop
being on my phone.

509
00:18:37.650 --> 00:18:39.820
Not to get frostbite.

510
00:18:41.050 --> 00:18:42.850
If you can’t confront
the searing pain of truth.

511
00:18:42.960 --> 00:18:44.160
you’re welcome to leave. Jeff.

512
00:18:45.020 --> 00:18:47.190
You know what?
Screw this.

513
00:18:49.230 --> 00:18:51.930
It’s a gift when the unfaithful
make themselves known.

514
00:18:53.800 --> 00:18:56.640
Now. it is time
to get at the truth.

515
00:18:58.170 --> 00:19:01.240
Dylan. do you want to quit
like Jeff. or continue?

516
00:19:01.840 --> 00:19:02.310
I’ll continue.

517
00:19:03.080 --> 00:19:04.320
Good. Now please tell us.

518
00:19:07.410 --> 00:19:09.880
Why have you come to The Apiary?

519
00:19:09.980 --> 00:19:13.120
I’ve been pretty lost ever
since my divorce was finalized

520
00:19:13.220 --> 00:19:14.120
A couple of weeks ago

521
00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:16.220
it was my seven-year-old’s
basketball game.

522
00:19:17.160 --> 00:19:19.300
And uh. well.
I was on my phone

523
00:19:20.530 --> 00:19:21.730
and all of a sudden.
the crowd started cheering.

524
00:19:21.830 --> 00:19:23.100
So I looked up and...

525
00:19:24.760 --> 00:19:26.200
he just scored his first basket.

526
00:19:27.930 --> 00:19:28.930
I missed it.

527
00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:31.170
And he knew I missed it.

528
00:19:32.070 --> 00:19:33.200
As a parent. you just

529
00:19:34.340 --> 00:19:35.840
you don’t get those
memories back. you know?

530
00:19:35.940 --> 00:19:37.810
Your escapism caused you
to let him down.

531
00:19:37.910 --> 00:19:40.850
Yeah. So anyway. I ran into
an old high school buddy

532
00:19:40.950 --> 00:19:42.350
the other day. and he told me
about The Apiary.

533
00:19:43.520 --> 00:19:44.760
It sounded like it was
exactly what I needed.

534
00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:47.220
Actually. I thought
I might find him here.

535
00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:49.160
He might be.
What’s his name?

536
00:19:49.250 --> 00:19:50.250
Cornelius Cooper.

537
00:19:52.020 --> 00:19:53.050
I don’t know that name.

538
00:19:53.890 --> 00:19:55.290
That concludes this session.

539
00:19:56.090 --> 00:19:56.990
You may remove your hands.

540
00:19:58.260 --> 00:20:00.230
We now enter an open period
where you are encouraged

541
00:20:01.070 --> 00:20:02.270
to build new neural pathways

542
00:20:02.370 --> 00:20:03.670
by interacting
with your community.

543
00:20:03.770 --> 00:20:06.870
So take this time to connect
with your Apiary members.

544
00:20:08.140 --> 00:20:10.880
Have you met someone
named Cornelius?

545
00:20:10.980 --> 00:20:12.250
I do not know that name.

546
00:20:13.610 --> 00:20:15.280
I know someone named Cornelius.
Have you seen him here?

547
00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:17.020
I do not know that name.

548
00:20:18.020 --> 00:20:19.820
Do you know someone
named Cornelius?

549
00:20:21.190 --> 00:20:22.190
I do not know that name.

550
00:20:22.290 --> 00:20:24.390
His name is Cornelius.
Have you seen him here?

551
00:20:25.120 --> 00:20:26.190
I do not know that name.

552
00:20:27.130 --> 00:20:28.730
Uh. Excuse me.

553
00:20:30.160 --> 00:20:32.330
Why do you have to bring
me over here to make a scene?

554
00:20:32.430 --> 00:20:33.870
To not be
in front of everybody.

555
00:20:33.970 --> 00:20:35.100
So just talk to me right now.

556
00:20:35.200 --> 00:20:36.030
I’m talking to you.

557
00:20:36.130 --> 00:20:37.200
I don’t know what
you want me to say.

558
00:20:37.300 --> 00:20:39.100
I want you
to tell me the truth!

559
00:20:39.200 --> 00:20:40.100
What is your problem?

560
00:20:40.210 --> 00:20:41.140
I don’t know.

561
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:42.810
I don’t want to do it. okay?
It’s too soon.

562
00:20:42.910 --> 00:20:44.950
Okay. If you’re doubtful. you
need to raise your concerns

563
00:20:45.040 --> 00:20:46.110
to Celeste
at the meeting tonight.

564
00:20:46.210 --> 00:20:48.380
- I’m not doubtful.
- - Then enough!

565
00:20:49.010 --> 00:20:50.040
Get back to work.

566
00:20:56.990 --> 00:20:58.290
Did you have to pick
the most treacherous

567
00:20:59.020 --> 00:20:59.750
meeting spot possible?

568
00:20:59.860 --> 00:21:01.100
I saw four snakes
on the way here.

569
00:21:01.190 --> 00:21:02.890
You did not see
four snakes.

570
00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:04.300
Four twigs that looked
like snakes. but still.

571
00:21:05.530 --> 00:21:06.330
There’s cameras everywhere
except for right here.

572
00:21:06.970 --> 00:21:08.070
I noticed that.

573
00:21:08.170 --> 00:21:09.840
- How was your first workshop?
- No finger chopping.

574
00:21:09.940 --> 00:21:12.340
It was more high school
drama class than Jonestown.

575
00:21:12.440 --> 00:21:13.610
- How about you?
- Yeah.

576
00:21:13.710 --> 00:21:15.280
They made us put our arms
in ice cold water.

577
00:21:15.370 --> 00:21:16.140
and then
they kicked this guy out

578
00:21:16.240 --> 00:21:17.440
’cause he couldn’t
take it anymore.

579
00:21:18.180 --> 00:21:19.310
The mind games begin.

580
00:21:19.410 --> 00:21:22.250
Yeah. Oh. but after. I overheard
Kurt and Fiona talking.

581
00:21:22.350 --> 00:21:24.450
Fiona said something about
something being too soon.

582
00:21:25.880 --> 00:21:27.180
So then Kurt told her to bring
it up at some meeting tonight.

583
00:21:27.290 --> 00:21:28.420
Think it was a meeting
of the worker bees?

584
00:21:29.050 --> 00:21:29.920
Sounds like it.

585
00:21:30.020 --> 00:21:31.290
Okay. well. how about Cornelius?

586
00:21:31.390 --> 00:21:34.290
Every person I asked about him
said "I do not know that name".

587
00:21:35.330 --> 00:21:36.460
Wait. did they say
it just like that?

588
00:21:36.560 --> 00:21:38.230
Yep. Every single one of them.

589
00:21:38.330 --> 00:21:39.130
Just like me.

590
00:21:39.230 --> 00:21:40.400
Someone’s telling
them to say that.

591
00:21:41.270 --> 00:21:42.510
You think they’re brainwashed?

592
00:21:42.600 --> 00:21:44.100
I don’t know. but we need to
check out that meeting tonight.

593
00:21:44.200 --> 00:21:46.200
Okay. but first. I need
to get to the property line.

594
00:21:46.310 --> 00:21:48.250
Li kept insisting that we
have a way of communicating.

595
00:21:48.340 --> 00:21:50.410
so I had Simmons bury
a burner phone out there.

596
00:21:50.510 --> 00:21:53.450
Okay. I’ll be right back.
Just stay in your tent.

597
00:22:08.230 --> 00:22:09.870
What did people
do before phones?

598
00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:16.270
Ellis. where are you?

599
00:22:16.370 --> 00:22:19.870
Cult leader and minions spotted
going to a secret meeting.

600
00:22:21.310 --> 00:22:22.340
Okay.

601
00:22:37.920 --> 00:22:40.120
You are my worker bees.

602
00:22:40.230 --> 00:22:42.170
My faithful inner circle.

603
00:22:42.260 --> 00:22:44.200
But I can feel you questioning.

604
00:22:44.300 --> 00:22:45.500
Why did this happen?

605
00:22:46.400 --> 00:22:48.140
Why. Cornelius?

606
00:22:48.230 --> 00:22:50.300
So they do know Cornelius.

607
00:22:51.570 --> 00:22:53.340
I feel your pain.
So let’s take a moment.

608
00:22:54.870 --> 00:22:55.940
Let us close our eyes.

609
00:22:56.980 --> 00:22:58.550
Max! Max?

610
00:23:03.050 --> 00:23:05.350
Cornelius. we remember you.

611
00:23:05.450 --> 00:23:08.220
Your strength.
your wit. your dedication.

612
00:23:08.320 --> 00:23:12.220
You were a diligent worker bee
who wanted your hive to thrive.

613
00:23:12.320 --> 00:23:14.560
And we thank you
for your sacrifice.

614
00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:16.560
and for the bounty
that you left behind.

615
00:23:19.330 --> 00:23:20.430
Let us open our eyes.

616
00:23:21.530 --> 00:23:24.400
Cornelius’s sacrifice
cannot be in vain.

617
00:23:24.500 --> 00:23:27.440
Tomorrow’s harvest will go
forward as planned.

618
00:23:27.540 --> 00:23:30.510
And Kurt. my most trusted
friend and advisor.

619
00:23:31.380 --> 00:23:32.510
you will take Cornelius’s place.

620
00:23:32.610 --> 00:23:34.580
I would be honoured.
my queen.

621
00:23:34.680 --> 00:23:37.380
Guess we know who the teacher’s
pet is. don’t we. Kurt?

622
00:23:38.920 --> 00:23:39.590
What are you doing?

623
00:23:45.590 --> 00:23:46.860
What do you think you’re doing?

624
00:23:46.960 --> 00:23:49.430
Would you believe I needed
to borrow a cup of sugar?

625
00:23:49.530 --> 00:23:50.300
You’re not supposed to be

626
00:23:50.400 --> 00:23:52.500
outside of
your lodging at night.

627
00:23:52.600 --> 00:23:54.140
Fiona. why is everyone
pretending

628
00:23:54.230 --> 00:23:56.030
they don’t know who
Cornelius is?

629
00:23:56.130 --> 00:23:56.930
Including you.

630
00:23:59.070 --> 00:24:00.410
You knew him. didn’t you?

631
00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:02.480
I more than knew him.

632
00:24:06.610 --> 00:24:07.810
We were in love.

633
00:24:07.910 --> 00:24:10.480
But why did you tell me
you didn’t know that name?

634
00:24:10.580 --> 00:24:11.580
That’s what we’re told to say.

635
00:24:11.680 --> 00:24:15.020
When someone leaves. they
no longer exist to us.

636
00:24:15.120 --> 00:24:17.590
But Cornelius didn’t
just leave. did he?

637
00:24:17.690 --> 00:24:19.290
What happened to him?

638
00:24:19.390 --> 00:24:21.560
Fiona. I know you’re scared.
but you can trust me.

639
00:24:21.660 --> 00:24:22.930
I want to help.

640
00:24:24.200 --> 00:24:27.170
I did something... terrible.

641
00:24:27.270 --> 00:24:28.170
I...

642
00:24:29.570 --> 00:24:31.270
You need to leave now.

643
00:24:31.370 --> 00:24:33.210
Meet me at the greenhouse
in an hour.

644
00:24:40.210 --> 00:24:42.380
It’s been over an hour.
She’s not coming. Max.

645
00:24:42.480 --> 00:24:43.450
I hope she’s okay.

646
00:24:43.550 --> 00:24:45.490
What if they chopped off
her finger? Or worse?

647
00:24:45.580 --> 00:24:47.320
At this point. she probably
ratted you out.

648
00:24:47.420 --> 00:24:49.420
You should have just stayed
in the tent like I told you to.

649
00:24:49.520 --> 00:24:51.520
At least now we know Cornelius
was here.

650
00:24:51.620 --> 00:24:54.090
Look. Fiona said that she
did something terrible. right?

651
00:24:54.190 --> 00:24:55.490
If she did kill Cornelius.

652
00:24:55.590 --> 00:24:57.260
maybe she got cold feet
about confessing.

653
00:24:57.360 --> 00:24:59.360
Well. she does have
Manson groupie energy.

654
00:24:59.460 --> 00:25:01.600
Oh. and that harvest
is happening tomorrow.

655
00:25:01.700 --> 00:25:02.830
We need to find out
what that is.

656
00:25:02.930 --> 00:25:04.670
I think it’s time
we leapfrog these minions

657
00:25:05.770 --> 00:25:06.600
and get in with
the head honcho. Celeste.

658
00:25:07.610 --> 00:25:08.510
Okay. How do you suggest
we do that?

659
00:25:08.610 --> 00:25:10.550
Allow me to refer to
<i> The Art of War</i> .

660
00:25:10.640 --> 00:25:12.110
Enlighten me. please.

661
00:25:12.210 --> 00:25:14.410
Sun Tzu says attacking
your opponent’s city

662
00:25:14.510 --> 00:25:16.080
isn’t nearly as effective

663
00:25:16.180 --> 00:25:18.250
as weakening
your opponent’s alliances.

664
00:25:18.350 --> 00:25:19.590
- Kurt.
- Bingo.

665
00:25:19.680 --> 00:25:21.620
Except Kurt worships Celeste.

666
00:25:21.720 --> 00:25:23.460
He even calls her his queen.

667
00:25:23.560 --> 00:25:25.560
Which you’re more than welcome
to call me. by the way.

668
00:25:25.660 --> 00:25:26.560
Don’t hold your breath.

669
00:25:27.290 --> 00:25:28.220
Okay. You got any ideas?

670
00:25:28.330 --> 00:25:29.970
Of course.
Pass me your phone.

671
00:25:31.660 --> 00:25:33.260
You got Candy crush
on this thing?

672
00:25:33.370 --> 00:25:35.370
No. just the one with a snake.

673
00:25:43.810 --> 00:25:44.610
Good morning. Beth.

674
00:25:45.180 --> 00:25:46.420
Celeste! Hi!

675
00:25:47.410 --> 00:25:49.980
There you are.
Watching me sleep.

676
00:25:50.650 --> 00:25:51.580
Why?

677
00:25:53.080 --> 00:25:54.550
Let’s take a walk.

678
00:26:05.130 --> 00:26:06.470
Um. hey.

679
00:26:07.800 --> 00:26:10.270
Look. my stomach’s been
a little off since last night.

680
00:26:10.370 --> 00:26:11.710
so. uh. if it’s cool with you.

681
00:26:11.800 --> 00:26:13.700
I think I might just
sit this one out.

682
00:26:13.810 --> 00:26:15.710
I don’t know which end
it’s coming out of. you know?

683
00:26:16.710 --> 00:26:17.580
Let us know
if you need anything.

684
00:26:17.680 --> 00:26:18.510
Okay. Thanks.

685
00:27:52.800 --> 00:27:55.500
You know. I have been
all over the world.

686
00:27:55.610 --> 00:27:58.450
Nothing beats the culinary
simplicity of a street dog.

687
00:27:58.540 --> 00:27:59.440
Amen.

688
00:28:00.580 --> 00:28:02.780
I am glad you called me. George.

689
00:28:02.880 --> 00:28:04.350
What’s on your mind?

690
00:28:04.450 --> 00:28:05.720
Well. I was thinking about
what you said.

691
00:28:06.790 --> 00:28:08.690
and. um. if you want
to know the truth.

692
00:28:09.790 --> 00:28:11.530
I’ve been living a lie.

693
00:28:11.620 --> 00:28:12.420
What do you mean?

694
00:28:12.520 --> 00:28:14.360
I haven’t been honest
with myself.

695
00:28:14.460 --> 00:28:15.730
Or you.

696
00:28:17.060 --> 00:28:19.500
But I stand up there in
front of my counselling group.

697
00:28:19.600 --> 00:28:22.540
preaching like some
prison Socrates.

698
00:28:22.630 --> 00:28:25.800
about hope and resilience
and second chances.

699
00:28:25.900 --> 00:28:27.600
It’s all very blue sky.
and they lap it up.

700
00:28:27.710 --> 00:28:29.650
Well. that’s good. George.
They need that.

701
00:28:29.740 --> 00:28:30.810
But it’s all BS.

702
00:28:31.840 --> 00:28:32.970
You see. I’ve always
been a planner.

703
00:28:33.080 --> 00:28:35.420
I’ve needed everything planned
out to the last detail.

704
00:28:35.510 --> 00:28:37.310
That’s how you run
a successful con.

705
00:28:37.420 --> 00:28:38.320
A successful life.

706
00:28:38.420 --> 00:28:40.890
So then I walk out
of those prison gates

707
00:28:41.750 --> 00:28:42.820
and nothing’s running to plan.

708
00:28:43.590 --> 00:28:44.760
Everything’s topsy-turvy.

709
00:28:45.890 --> 00:28:47.760
If this was a con.
it would be a disaster.

710
00:28:47.860 --> 00:28:50.860
George. adjusting takes work.
It’s hard.

711
00:28:50.960 --> 00:28:53.560
Yeah. but I feel like I’m lying
to the guys inside.

712
00:28:53.670 --> 00:28:54.500
Like I’m a fraud.

713
00:28:54.600 --> 00:28:56.200
You’re not a fraud.
you’re a human.

714
00:28:57.340 --> 00:28:59.310
The fact that you can
show these guys hope

715
00:28:59.400 --> 00:29:00.570
while at the same time
still struggling

716
00:29:00.670 --> 00:29:01.840
with your own challenges?

717
00:29:02.840 --> 00:29:04.710
That’s not lying.
That’s leadership.

718
00:29:04.810 --> 00:29:06.780
- Or hypocrisy.
- No. It’s honesty.

719
00:29:07.880 --> 00:29:09.920
And if you can let them
see both sides.

720
00:29:10.010 --> 00:29:12.810
the man who doubts
and the man who believes.

721
00:29:12.920 --> 00:29:14.360
you give them something real.

722
00:29:15.890 --> 00:29:17.190
You want some gum?

723
00:29:17.820 --> 00:29:18.790
Oh. yeah. Thanks.

724
00:29:20.830 --> 00:29:22.700
You make it all sound so simple.

725
00:29:22.790 --> 00:29:24.590
Yeah. Yeah. it is simple.

726
00:29:25.630 --> 00:29:27.330
Huh.
Doesn’t mean it’s easy. though.

727
00:29:34.770 --> 00:29:38.470
Beth. do you know why I named
our movement The Apiary?

728
00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:41.280
I figured you
just really liked bees.

729
00:29:42.410 --> 00:29:44.410
It’s about what bees represent.

730
00:29:44.520 --> 00:29:46.960
Their focus is on the growth
of the whole community.

731
00:29:48.020 --> 00:29:48.820
And wouldn’t the world be
a better place

732
00:29:48.920 --> 00:29:50.490
if we all lived like that?

733
00:29:51.060 --> 00:29:51.890
Absolutely.

734
00:29:51.990 --> 00:29:52.920
Beth. I know you came here

735
00:29:53.020 --> 00:29:55.190
seeking connection
and community.

736
00:29:55.960 --> 00:29:56.860
and we welcomed you in.

737
00:29:57.730 --> 00:29:58.600
And I really appreciate that.

738
00:29:58.700 --> 00:29:59.940
Then why did you break my rules

739
00:30:00.900 --> 00:30:02.400
and go out
after curfew last night?

740
00:30:02.500 --> 00:30:03.840
How did you find out?

741
00:30:03.940 --> 00:30:06.380
Fiona mentioned
that she had run into you.

742
00:30:06.470 --> 00:30:07.570
Is she okay?

743
00:30:07.670 --> 00:30:08.940
I haven’t seen her since then.

744
00:30:09.040 --> 00:30:11.540
She’s had a tough time recently.

745
00:30:11.640 --> 00:30:12.770
She’s resting.

746
00:30:13.980 --> 00:30:16.450
I know you were spying
on the meeting house.

747
00:30:17.950 --> 00:30:19.390
Why?

748
00:30:19.480 --> 00:30:20.850
I don’t want to get anyone
in trouble.

749
00:30:21.620 --> 00:30:22.860
Beth. you can trust me.

750
00:30:22.950 --> 00:30:24.750
The question is.
can I trust you?

751
00:30:26.460 --> 00:30:28.560
I heard something outside
my tent.

752
00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:30.000
so I went to go check it out.

753
00:30:31.360 --> 00:30:34.860
And that’s when I saw that
Dylan guy talking to someone.

754
00:30:35.670 --> 00:30:37.010
Who is he speaking with?

755
00:30:37.700 --> 00:30:38.870
Kurt.

756
00:30:40.540 --> 00:30:43.310
Hello. Celeste. and... Beth.

757
00:30:46.480 --> 00:30:47.680
Here he is.

758
00:30:47.780 --> 00:30:48.610
Thank you.

759
00:30:50.720 --> 00:30:51.720
Celeste. what is going on?

760
00:30:51.820 --> 00:30:54.320
Beth. where did you say
that Kurt put the phone?

761
00:30:56.090 --> 00:30:57.630
I do not have a phone.

762
00:31:00.060 --> 00:31:01.800
Celeste. that is not mine.

763
00:31:01.890 --> 00:31:02.520
No?

764
00:31:02.630 --> 00:31:04.000
Try dialing the last number.

765
00:31:12.970 --> 00:31:14.070
Good morning. City Gazette.

766
00:31:14.170 --> 00:31:16.310
<i>This is Dylan Smith’s desk.
How can I help you?</i>

767
00:31:17.780 --> 00:31:19.720
You’re a journalist.
Is this right?

768
00:31:19.810 --> 00:31:20.910
I’ve been working
with Kurt for months

769
00:31:21.750 --> 00:31:22.750
on an exposé on The Apiary.

770
00:31:22.850 --> 00:31:23.680
That is a lie.

771
00:31:24.520 --> 00:31:25.990
Do not believe him. Celeste.

772
00:31:26.080 --> 00:31:27.780
It’s over. man.
We’re burned. Okay?

773
00:31:27.890 --> 00:31:29.830
I’m so sorry. Celeste.

774
00:31:29.920 --> 00:31:31.020
Kurt. how could you?

775
00:31:31.120 --> 00:31:32.790
You’re gonna believe her
over me?

776
00:31:32.890 --> 00:31:34.630
It’s done. man.
We tried and we failed--

777
00:31:34.730 --> 00:31:35.560
Shut up!

778
00:31:36.690 --> 00:31:37.660
Kurt.

779
00:31:38.700 --> 00:31:41.070
I can’t believe
I ever trusted you.

780
00:31:41.170 --> 00:31:42.000
None of it is true.

781
00:31:42.870 --> 00:31:43.800
You know me.

782
00:31:44.340 --> 00:31:45.680
I am Kurt.

783
00:31:46.400 --> 00:31:48.040
I do not know that name.

784
00:31:54.150 --> 00:31:55.890
All right. all right.

785
00:31:57.050 --> 00:31:58.420
Who the hell are you?

786
00:32:00.420 --> 00:32:02.790
Why are you doing this to me?

787
00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:06.600
I’m a cop. dumbass.

788
00:32:07.560 --> 00:32:08.660
I’m asking
the questions now. Kurt.

789
00:32:09.730 --> 00:32:10.930
Who killed Cornelius?

790
00:32:14.530 --> 00:32:16.070
I can’t believe
Kurt betrayed me.

791
00:32:16.170 --> 00:32:17.710
How could I have missed that?

792
00:32:17.800 --> 00:32:20.870
It’s not your fault.
You’re an amazing leader.

793
00:32:20.970 --> 00:32:22.970
Kurt took advantage
of your generosity.

794
00:32:23.570 --> 00:32:24.500
Thank you. Beth.

795
00:32:24.610 --> 00:32:27.010
I am so grateful
my intuition led me to you.

796
00:32:27.950 --> 00:32:29.320
Well. anything you need.
I’m here.

797
00:32:29.810 --> 00:32:31.550
My queen.

798
00:32:34.720 --> 00:32:36.790
I’m glad to hear that.

799
00:32:36.890 --> 00:32:38.090
because I would like you
to take part

800
00:32:38.820 --> 00:32:39.720
in tonight’s harvest.

801
00:32:39.820 --> 00:32:42.660
Sure. What are we harvesting?

802
00:32:42.760 --> 00:32:43.830
I’m not very good at gardening.

803
00:32:43.930 --> 00:32:45.770
I’ve killed all my houseplants.

804
00:32:45.860 --> 00:32:48.500
All will be revealed.
But for now. just know

805
00:32:49.330 --> 00:32:51.030
that great things await you.

806
00:32:51.870 --> 00:32:52.970
Kurt’s lawyered up.

807
00:32:53.070 --> 00:32:53.800
He’s not talking.

808
00:32:53.910 --> 00:32:55.080
Did you ask about
the cult sex?

809
00:32:55.170 --> 00:32:56.770
No. I didn’t ask
about the cult sex.

810
00:32:56.870 --> 00:32:58.840
And you call yourself
a detective. It’s wild.

811
00:32:58.940 --> 00:33:00.840
What did you two
dig up about Kurt?

812
00:33:00.950 --> 00:33:02.890
Yeah. well.
when Kurt met Celeste

813
00:33:02.980 --> 00:33:04.580
he was working
at a tech company. too.

814
00:33:04.680 --> 00:33:07.580
Shortly after he quit.
the company was broken into.

815
00:33:07.690 --> 00:33:10.030
Thieves walked away with
half a million in crypto.

816
00:33:10.120 --> 00:33:11.790
No arrests. no answers.

817
00:33:11.890 --> 00:33:12.920
Then we looked
into Fiona

818
00:33:13.020 --> 00:33:15.620
and her former company
was robbed just last week.

819
00:33:15.730 --> 00:33:17.100
Over a million
in crypto was stolen.

820
00:33:17.900 --> 00:33:19.070
But it’s digital currency.

821
00:33:19.160 --> 00:33:21.130
Why physically break in
when you can just hack it?

822
00:33:22.430 --> 00:33:24.070
The money is digital.
but the storage isn’t always.

823
00:33:25.300 --> 00:33:26.770
It’s like a crypto wallet.
It’s a physical drive.

824
00:33:26.870 --> 00:33:28.710
So if you put crypto
onto the wallet.

825
00:33:28.810 --> 00:33:30.080
and you forget the password?

826
00:33:30.840 --> 00:33:31.640
You’re done for.

827
00:33:31.740 --> 00:33:32.840
That happened
to me once.

828
00:33:32.940 --> 00:33:35.740
I bought 50 bucks worth
of crypto back in 2009.

829
00:33:35.850 --> 00:33:38.050
Put it on one of those things.
Forgot the password.

830
00:33:38.150 --> 00:33:40.150
I still have it at home.
I just use it as a paperweight.

831
00:33:40.250 --> 00:33:41.820
Do you remember what
kind of crypto it was?

832
00:33:41.920 --> 00:33:42.750
I think it was called like.

833
00:33:42.850 --> 00:33:44.150
"small change" or
"teeny tiny money".

834
00:33:44.920 --> 00:33:45.620
- Bitcoin?
- Bitcoin.

835
00:33:46.220 --> 00:33:47.220
Yeah. That’s it.

836
00:33:47.330 --> 00:33:49.170
Yates. that’s worth like
a lot of money right now.

837
00:33:49.890 --> 00:33:50.760
Oh yeah. Maybe I’m rich.

838
00:33:50.860 --> 00:33:52.060
Can we get back
to the case here.

839
00:33:52.160 --> 00:33:54.560
Yeah. So tech companies
build walls.

840
00:33:54.670 --> 00:33:56.110
internal servers
you can’t access

841
00:33:57.370 --> 00:33:58.940
from outside the building.
It keeps the hackers out.

842
00:33:59.040 --> 00:34:00.840
Yeah. like in the case of
Fiona’s former workplace.

843
00:34:00.940 --> 00:34:02.110
Exactly. They got into
the building.

844
00:34:02.210 --> 00:34:04.050
they got into the computers.
they transferred the money.

845
00:34:04.840 --> 00:34:05.940
But they made one mistake.

846
00:34:06.040 --> 00:34:07.780
They didn’t realize there
was an armed guard on duty.

847
00:34:07.880 --> 00:34:10.680
They got away. but the security
guard got some shots off.

848
00:34:10.780 --> 00:34:11.780
He thought he only hit the van.

849
00:34:11.880 --> 00:34:13.010
- Was the van white?
- Yep.

850
00:34:13.120 --> 00:34:14.020
The painted van that you found

851
00:34:14.120 --> 00:34:15.490
matched the security guard’s
description.

852
00:34:15.590 --> 00:34:17.830
Ballistics just came back
on the bullet you found.

853
00:34:17.920 --> 00:34:19.120
Thanks. Okay.

854
00:34:19.220 --> 00:34:21.860
The bullet from the van and
the one that killed Cornelius

855
00:34:21.960 --> 00:34:23.900
both came from
the security guard’s gun.

856
00:34:24.000 --> 00:34:26.100
So Cornelius was killed
by the security guard

857
00:34:27.070 --> 00:34:28.100
and not by someone
in The Apiary.

858
00:34:28.830 --> 00:34:29.600
Did Cornelius act alone?

859
00:34:29.700 --> 00:34:30.770
Guard said there
was three of them.

860
00:34:30.870 --> 00:34:31.800
Cornelius was one.

861
00:34:31.900 --> 00:34:34.700
The other two.
most likely from The Apiary.

862
00:34:34.810 --> 00:34:37.050
Okay. They kept talking about
a harvest happening tonight.

863
00:34:37.140 --> 00:34:39.940
What if harvest is just
a code word for robbery?

864
00:34:40.040 --> 00:34:41.040
Based on the pattern.
I’d say they’re at

865
00:34:41.150 --> 00:34:43.050
one of the tech companies
they used to work for.

866
00:34:43.150 --> 00:34:44.650
Cornelius used to
work for SociaScope.

867
00:34:44.750 --> 00:34:46.120
- They haven’t been hit.
- Yeah. Yet.

868
00:34:47.920 --> 00:34:50.190
I’m so honoured to be
doing this with you. Celeste.

869
00:34:50.290 --> 00:34:52.130
But I’m curious.
Where are we going?

870
00:34:52.220 --> 00:34:54.820
Beth. when I first created
The Apiary.

871
00:34:54.930 --> 00:34:56.730
I was proud of what
we had accomplished

872
00:34:56.830 --> 00:34:59.230
on the personal level.
but it wasn’t enough.

873
00:35:00.500 --> 00:35:02.000
If I wanted to undo
the wrongs of the tech world.

874
00:35:02.100 --> 00:35:03.000
I had to hurt them.

875
00:35:03.100 --> 00:35:05.640
But they only care
about the bottom line.

876
00:35:05.740 --> 00:35:07.110
So my worker bees and I

877
00:35:08.310 --> 00:35:10.110
decided to hit these companies
where it hurts.

878
00:35:10.710 --> 00:35:11.480
Their wallets.

879
00:35:11.580 --> 00:35:13.080
So we’re gonna rob somebody?

880
00:35:13.180 --> 00:35:14.310
Harvest.

881
00:35:14.410 --> 00:35:17.650
We take from evil forces
to fund The Apiary’s good work.

882
00:35:18.380 --> 00:35:19.110
We’re here.

883
00:35:19.880 --> 00:35:21.050
Okay. so we’re gonna rob-

884
00:35:21.150 --> 00:35:24.720
Sorry. "harvest"
the SociaScope offices. why?

885
00:35:25.920 --> 00:35:27.990
Beth. let me tell you
the story of Cornelius.

886
00:35:28.090 --> 00:35:29.860
our most faithful worker bee.

887
00:35:36.670 --> 00:35:38.270
And just as Cornelius
was getting into the van.

888
00:35:39.270 --> 00:35:40.170
he was shot by
the security guard.

889
00:35:41.040 --> 00:35:42.170
He bled out quickly.

890
00:35:42.870 --> 00:35:44.000
Well. that’s awful.

891
00:35:44.840 --> 00:35:45.710
It is.

892
00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:47.650
Cornelius was
dedicated to the cause.

893
00:35:48.510 --> 00:35:50.550
Tonight we honour his sacrifice.

894
00:35:51.680 --> 00:35:54.120
And there’s not any
security here tonight?

895
00:35:54.220 --> 00:35:57.720
SociaScope operates entirely
on a digital security system.

896
00:35:58.860 --> 00:36:01.200
He gave us the tools
to override that system.

897
00:36:01.290 --> 00:36:03.690
He also cloned
his boss’s access card.

898
00:36:06.330 --> 00:36:07.260
Shall we?

899
00:36:19.010 --> 00:36:19.940
Now sit.

900
00:36:27.390 --> 00:36:32.000
Enter password HX76B49.

901
00:36:32.090 --> 00:36:33.990
It’s a crypto account
that can only be accessed

902
00:36:34.090 --> 00:36:34.960
by this computer.

903
00:36:35.060 --> 00:36:35.990
Its touch ID.

904
00:36:36.090 --> 00:36:38.130
It won’t recognize
my fingerprints or yours.

905
00:36:38.230 --> 00:36:39.570
No. it won’t.

906
00:36:40.730 --> 00:36:43.630
But it will recognize
Cornelius’s fingerprint.

907
00:36:50.580 --> 00:36:52.550
Why do you have
Cornelius’s finger?

908
00:36:53.580 --> 00:36:54.980
Before Cornelius quit
at SociaScope.

909
00:36:55.080 --> 00:36:57.050
he reprogrammed
the internal server

910
00:36:57.150 --> 00:36:59.750
so that his fingerprint
would allow him access

911
00:36:59.850 --> 00:37:01.850
to his boss’s personal
crypto account.

912
00:37:03.190 --> 00:37:05.360
When Cornelius was killed.
we took emergency measures.

913
00:37:05.460 --> 00:37:07.030
So you cut off
a dead dude’s finger?

914
00:37:07.120 --> 00:37:08.920
I asked Fiona to do it.
She complied.

915
00:37:09.030 --> 00:37:11.100
That’s the terrible thing
that Fiona did.

916
00:37:11.200 --> 00:37:12.300
Now take the finger.

917
00:37:12.400 --> 00:37:13.470
You want me to touch that thing?

918
00:37:13.560 --> 00:37:15.260
If you want to ascend
to the next level

919
00:37:16.370 --> 00:37:17.270
and become a member
of my inner circle.

920
00:37:17.370 --> 00:37:18.910
you must complete this task.

921
00:37:25.140 --> 00:37:26.640
Sorry. Cornelius.

922
00:37:30.950 --> 00:37:32.750
Okay. It’s done.

923
00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:39.160
Whoa. A lot of money
and no paper trail.

924
00:37:39.260 --> 00:37:43.130
Now. transfer 20 million
crypto into this account.

925
00:37:52.200 --> 00:37:54.040
- So?
- Almost.

926
00:37:54.840 --> 00:37:55.770
And...

927
00:37:57.210 --> 00:37:58.750
- Done.
- Great work.

928
00:37:59.440 --> 00:38:00.680
Let’s go.

929
00:38:11.190 --> 00:38:12.290
Don’t move!

930
00:38:13.420 --> 00:38:14.960
Hands in the air now!

931
00:38:15.960 --> 00:38:17.760
Celeste Rainier.
you’re under arrest.

932
00:38:18.830 --> 00:38:20.300
Easy on her. fellas.

933
00:38:20.400 --> 00:38:23.240
She’s had a long day
of exploiting people.

934
00:38:23.330 --> 00:38:24.300
You traitor!

935
00:38:24.400 --> 00:38:26.700
That’s what you get
for giving me the finger.

936
00:38:32.010 --> 00:38:33.380
Hey. You okay?

937
00:38:34.710 --> 00:38:36.380
Yeah. I’m fine. but...
do you have any hand sanitizer?

938
00:38:37.420 --> 00:38:38.420
Yeah. I think I got some
in the car. Why?

939
00:38:38.520 --> 00:38:40.120
Okay. ’cause I’m gonna
need a gallon of it.

940
00:38:40.220 --> 00:38:41.090
I’m gonna bathe in it.

941
00:38:44.260 --> 00:38:45.160
Good work. everyone.

942
00:38:45.260 --> 00:38:47.360
The Apiary has officially
been shut down.

943
00:38:47.960 --> 00:38:48.430
Where’s Fiona?

944
00:38:48.530 --> 00:38:49.560
She’s fine.

945
00:38:49.660 --> 00:38:51.100
We found her
in one of the staff houses

946
00:38:51.200 --> 00:38:53.070
watching hours
of indoctrination videos.

947
00:38:53.160 --> 00:38:54.400
It’s what Celeste
called "rejuvenation".

948
00:38:55.530 --> 00:38:56.300
Look. I know she was
part of the robberies.

949
00:38:56.400 --> 00:38:57.400
but she was brainwashed.

950
00:38:58.270 --> 00:38:59.100
Can we just get her some help?

951
00:38:59.200 --> 00:39:00.330
Yes. Definitely.

952
00:39:01.370 --> 00:39:03.170
Our psychiatrist
is evaluating her now.

953
00:39:03.270 --> 00:39:05.210
And Tess is talking
to other Apiary members

954
00:39:05.310 --> 00:39:07.180
about her class action lawsuit.

955
00:39:07.280 --> 00:39:10.150
Okay. that’s all well
and good. but. uh...

956
00:39:10.250 --> 00:39:13.220
Come on.
was there seriously... no sex?

957
00:39:13.320 --> 00:39:14.490
Oh my God. Yates. no.

958
00:39:14.590 --> 00:39:16.060
There’s no sex. okay?

959
00:39:16.150 --> 00:39:18.120
Damn it.
What kind of cult was this?

960
00:39:20.390 --> 00:39:21.490
Amateur hour.

961
00:39:22.830 --> 00:39:25.400
Great.
She’s gonna be grumpy all night

962
00:39:26.560 --> 00:39:27.390
unless I get a chimichangas
and a beef dip.

963
00:39:28.230 --> 00:39:29.200
You guys have a good night.

964
00:39:29.300 --> 00:39:29.970
Yeah.

965
00:39:30.840 --> 00:39:31.940
Look. uh.

966
00:39:32.040 --> 00:39:33.410
Jess and I are gonna get
some Chinese food on the boat.

967
00:39:34.040 --> 00:39:34.510
You wanna join?

968
00:39:35.370 --> 00:39:37.170
Uh... yeah.
That’d be great.

969
00:39:37.270 --> 00:39:39.410
Hey. Great idea setting up Kurt
to get close to Celeste.

970
00:39:40.140 --> 00:39:41.070
And that was good work

971
00:39:41.180 --> 00:39:42.310
figuring out where
they were gonna hit next.

972
00:39:43.510 --> 00:39:46.950
It’s almost like we’re one mind.
Like a hive mind.

973
00:39:47.050 --> 00:39:47.880
Maybe we should start a cult.

974
00:39:47.990 --> 00:39:49.360
Yeah. I think I’ll pass
on that one.

975
00:39:49.450 --> 00:39:51.190
Okay. fine.
I’ll start it with Marc.

976
00:39:51.290 --> 00:39:54.190
We’ll be two supreme beings
ruling with an iron fist.

977
00:39:56.260 --> 00:39:57.530
I’ve been
thinking about

978
00:39:57.630 --> 00:39:59.100
what I tell you guys every week.

979
00:39:59.200 --> 00:40:02.140
About second chances
and starting fresh.

980
00:40:02.230 --> 00:40:04.130
I’ve been giving out
that advice

981
00:40:04.240 --> 00:40:06.010
like it was candy
at Halloween.

982
00:40:06.100 --> 00:40:07.970
But lately
I’ve been wondering...

983
00:40:09.270 --> 00:40:10.440
do I even believe it?

984
00:40:11.340 --> 00:40:14.010
See. the truth is.
out there.

985
00:40:14.110 --> 00:40:15.510
I’ve been struggling.

986
00:40:15.610 --> 00:40:17.410
and I couldn’t
admit it at first.

987
00:40:17.520 --> 00:40:19.520
But then a friend of mine
said to me

988
00:40:20.520 --> 00:40:22.090
"no one expects
you to be perfect.

989
00:40:22.190 --> 00:40:24.060
they just expect you
to be honest."

990
00:40:24.160 --> 00:40:25.460
Wisdom doesn’t come from

991
00:40:26.720 --> 00:40:27.990
pretending you’ve got
everything all figured out.

992
00:40:29.090 --> 00:40:30.460
It comes from admitting
that you don’t.

993
00:40:31.260 --> 00:40:32.230
but moving forward anyway.

994
00:40:32.330 --> 00:40:34.870
You see. it’s not about
never stumbling.

995
00:40:35.930 --> 00:40:38.200
It’s about what we
do after we stumble.

996
00:40:43.070 --> 00:40:44.340
Jess. we’re home!

997
00:40:44.440 --> 00:40:45.570
We come bearing egg rolls!

998
00:40:45.680 --> 00:40:47.580
Must have missed this message.
Jessica’s running late.

999
00:40:48.580 --> 00:40:49.550
She says
to get started without her.

1000
00:40:49.650 --> 00:40:52.050
Oh. well. twist my rubber arm.
why don’t you?

1001
00:40:52.150 --> 00:40:54.190
Oh. Marc.

1002
00:40:54.290 --> 00:40:55.460
Hi. buddy.

1003
00:40:56.150 --> 00:40:58.490
Aww. his purrs.

1004
00:40:58.960 --> 00:40:59.490
Oh.

1005
00:41:00.190 --> 00:41:01.320
I missed you. Marc.

1006
00:41:02.630 --> 00:41:04.100
Awe.

1007
00:41:05.430 --> 00:41:06.360
It’s been a while since
you’ve been on the boat. huh?

1008
00:41:06.460 --> 00:41:08.600
You used to just
show up here all the time.

1009
00:41:09.470 --> 00:41:12.240
Yeah. well. things have changed.

1010
00:41:12.340 --> 00:41:13.470
What? Because of Jessica?

1011
00:41:13.570 --> 00:41:14.500
Not in a bad way.

1012
00:41:14.610 --> 00:41:17.280
I’m super happy
that you found her. but...

1013
00:41:18.440 --> 00:41:21.440
I know the deal.
I can’t just show up anymore.

1014
00:41:21.550 --> 00:41:24.490
So I might have
disconnected a little bit.

1015
00:41:24.580 --> 00:41:26.620
Look. I love Jessica. but

1016
00:41:26.720 --> 00:41:29.490
it doesn’t mean I should
have to choose between her

1017
00:41:30.250 --> 00:41:31.380
and my best friend.

1018
00:41:31.490 --> 00:41:32.390
I’m your best friend?

1019
00:41:34.090 --> 00:41:35.630
You’re my best friend. too.

1020
00:41:36.360 --> 00:41:37.430
Although. so is Ricky.

1021
00:41:37.530 --> 00:41:39.530
And George.
And. newly. my mom.

1022
00:41:40.500 --> 00:41:42.040
But a best friend
isn’t singular.

1023
00:41:42.130 --> 00:41:43.300
It’s like a tier. you know?

1024
00:41:43.400 --> 00:41:45.100
Just like Marc’s
right up there with you.

1025
00:41:45.200 --> 00:41:46.000
Right.

1026
00:41:50.610 --> 00:41:51.980
Oh. it’s Jessica.
Hold on.

1027
00:41:52.680 --> 00:41:54.420
Hello? Hey. you.

1028
00:41:57.280 --> 00:41:59.480
That- that is interesting. Huh.

1029
00:42:00.450 --> 00:42:02.320
Okay. Yeah.
I’ll see you later.

1030
00:42:02.420 --> 00:42:03.920
All right. Love you. Bye.

1031
00:42:06.020 --> 00:42:07.520
Jessica just got called
to cover a story.

1032
00:42:08.560 --> 00:42:09.630
Apparently.
the children’s hospital

1033
00:42:09.730 --> 00:42:11.670
that Toni was raising
money for just got a random

1034
00:42:11.760 --> 00:42:13.600
crypto donation for $20 million.

1035
00:42:14.300 --> 00:42:15.570
Huh. You don’t say.

1036
00:42:16.630 --> 00:42:17.630
Yeah. and the donation
was traced back

1037
00:42:17.740 --> 00:42:18.980
to Ronin from SociaScope.

1038
00:42:19.070 --> 00:42:22.340
Wasn’t he now being
investigated for tax evasion?

1039
00:42:22.440 --> 00:42:24.540
What if he dropped
a bunch of crypto

1040
00:42:24.640 --> 00:42:25.610
before the cops came knocking?

1041
00:42:26.210 --> 00:42:27.580
Max! Come on.

1042
00:42:27.680 --> 00:42:29.150
Did you steal
the money from Ronin?

1043
00:42:29.680 --> 00:42:30.580
I’m sorry.

1044
00:42:31.320 --> 00:42:32.220
I do not know that name.

1045
00:42:32.950 --> 00:42:34.080
Unbelievable.

1046
00:42:40.620 --> 00:42:42.990
Okay. my little
spaghetti monsters.

1047
00:42:44.230 --> 00:42:46.500
Who’s ready to make
a long-distance relationship

1048
00:42:46.600 --> 00:42:49.340
extremely uncomfortable?

1049
00:42:52.140 --> 00:42:54.180
Secure line. Adorable.

1050
00:42:57.110 --> 00:42:58.110
All right.

1051
00:42:58.210 --> 00:42:59.710
Fort Knox with a dial tone.

1052
00:43:01.110 --> 00:43:03.550
Let’s see how you feel about
a little temporary open house.

1053
00:43:05.250 --> 00:43:07.520
Don’t be shy.
It’s just a little handshake.

1054
00:43:07.620 --> 00:43:09.690
No dinner. no flowers.

1055
00:43:10.850 --> 00:43:12.590
Look at you cheating
on your firewall with me.

1056
00:43:12.690 --> 00:43:14.090
you naughty little minx.

1057
00:43:15.230 --> 00:43:17.570
Let’s see what you do
on the second date.

